Presenter Paul Martin and his team travel up and down the
nation looking for undiscovered treasures and forgotten
places that tell us about Britain's rich and astonishing history.
Paul visits Cragside House in Northumberland, home to one of
Victorian Britain's least remembered inventors, Lord William
Armstrong, who paved the way for domestic electricity.
Charlie Luxton spends the night in Lincoln Castle, in a 19th
century prison that was closed down 130 years ago; Clare
Balding travels to North Yorkshire to visit one of the country's
most beautiful and obscure ruined abbeys, and guest
reporter Charley Boorman uncovers the sunken remains of
Britain's very first submarine.
